devdoc.details: This is a Solidity smart contract written in the Ethereum blockchain programming language. It is named "MyContract" and contains two functions, "set" and "get", which allow a user to set and retrieve a string value, respectively. The contract is licensed under the MIT License and includes a custom development script that can be run with the command "dev-run-script file_path". When the contract is deployed, the initial value of the string is set to "default value".
devdoc.title: MyContract
